(577, 1, '2019-01-20 14:54:47', '2019-01-20 14:54:47', 'The annual International Exhibition specialized in Pharmaceuticals and Medical Equipment (VIETNAM MEDI PHARM EXPO) will take place from 11 to 13 August at Saigon Exhibition &amp; Convention Center (SECC) - 799 Nguyen Van Linh, District 7, HCMC.\r\nThis is an annual and prestigious exhibition held twice a year, August in Ho Chi Minh City. Ho Chi Minh City and December in Ho Chi Minh City. Hanoi.\r\n\r\nVietnam Medi Pharm Expo event in Ho Chi Minh City Ho Chi Minh has had a senior organization for 15 years, a long way in trade promotion activities of the Medicine and Pharmacy industry, significantly contributing to the connection of trade between domestic and foreign enterprises. Thereby, the modern medical and machinery works, advanced pharmaceuticals in the world have direct access to the public and private hospitals, and the whole country, as well as bring exciting commercial activities. between corporations and pharmaceutical companies is Vietnam''s strength with other countries in the world.\r\n\r\nMr. Hua Phu Doan - Vice Chairman and General Secretary of Ho Chi Minh City Medical Equipment Association. Ho Chi Minh said, Vietnam is emerging as an attractive destination for investors and pharmaceutical industry - medical equipment belonging to the most attractive investment sectors today. According to statistics, the revenue of Vietnam''s medical equipment market is estimated at about 800 million USD / year, this figure could reach 1.2 billion USD in 2016 and raise to 1.8 billion USD in 2018. The average growth rate in the period of 2016-2020 will reach about 18-20% / year. According to Assoc. Pham Le Tuan - Director of Department of Financial Planning (Ministry of Health), about 90% of medical equipment in Vietnam is imported. In particular, the countries that provide mainly medical equipment to Vietnam are Japan, Germany, the US, China and Singapore, accounting for about 55% of Vietnam''s import value of health workers.\r\n\r\nThus, it can be seen that the demand for investment in medical equipment in Vietnam will continue to increase and focus on image diagnosis devices, operating rooms, emergency resuscitation, intensive testing ... Investment in the site. High-tech health workers will focus mainly on large hospitals in big cities like (Ho Chi Minh City, Hanoi, Hue, Da Nang, Can Tho ...). Rang TP. Ho Chi Minh City in the next 3 years is estimated to invest about 900 million USD to upgrade health facilities for hospitals.\r\n\r\nIn Vietnam Medi Pharm Expo this year with the participation of 280 businesses are large corporations, reputable companies from 25 countries and territories such as the US, France, Germany, Italy, Japan, Pakistan, Urkaine, Belarus, Egypt, India, Hungary, Kazakhstan, Iran, Singapore, Korea, Taiwan, Thailand, China, ... with a scale of exhibiting 350 booths. Highlights are 10 national pavilions: Kazakhstan, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Iran, China, Taiwan, India, Pakistan and Vietnam.\r\n\r\nKazakhstan - the country that attended the Vietnam Medipharm Expo for the first time with the support of the Kazakhstan Ministry of Investment and Development displaying products: Pharmaceuticals; Tubes collecting vacuum blood; Medical products used only once, ... with the aim of expanding the Vietnamese market, as well as the desire to exchange experiences in the treatment of infertility under the coordination of Cho Ray Hospital. Ho Chi Minh.\r\n\r\nThe national pavilion from Iran is also the first time to join, the main product group introduced is Pharmaceutical. After President Truong Tan Sang''s trip in mid-March, Vietnam and Iran agreed to boost bilateral trade turnover to 2 billion USD in the next five years. Participation in this exhibition is also one of the new steps of Iranian businesses in seeking markets in Vietnam.\r\nFor a long time, Korean enterprises have always been reliable partners in the cooperation, technology transfer and supply of products in the biomedical, aesthetic, dental and functional rehabilitation sectors for hospitals and Vietnamese trading partners. At this year''s exhibition, more than 30 Korean enterprises, including many companies have participated in many years at the Exhibition such as Skysoftgel Company with pharmaceutical packaging and processing products. SG Healthcare, InBody, Dmetec, Personal Medical, Hwail, Bc World ... are companies that have trading partners in Vietnam. They participated in the exhibition with the aim to further reach customers who are companies, hospitals, clinics, cosmetic centers in the city. Ho Chi Minh City and neighboring provinces.\r\n\r\nIt is impossible not to mention Vietnamese corporations / businesses that are domestic producers, large import and export companies that are present at Vietnam Medi Pharm Expo for many years. The number of Vietnamese enterprises this year is higher than previous years with 200 enterprises.\r\n\r\nAnswering questions about the results achieved when participating in the exhibition, Mr. Qua That Chuan - Director of Nguyen Quoc Medical Equipment Joint Stock Company shared: "We have participated in Vienam Medi Pharm Expo for many years. , both in Hanoi and HCMC. Ho Chi Minh. We are a long-term business in this field, participating in the exhibition helps us improve our reputation, and the opportunity to meet customers are major hospitals in the city. Ho Chi Minh City and neighboring provinces. We realize that the exhibition has an ever-expanding scale, creating prestige', 'The 19th international medical and pharmaceutical exhibition VIETNAM MEDI PHARM EXPO', 'In Vietnam Medi Pharm Expo this year with the participation of 280 businesses are large corporations, reputable companies from 25 countries and territories such as the US, France, Germany, Italy, Japan, Pakistan, Urkaine, Belarus, Egypt, India, Hungary, Kazakhstan, Iran, Singapore, Korea, Taiwan, Thailand, China, ... with a scale of exhibiting 350 booths. Highlights are 10 national pavilions: Kazakhstan, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Iran, China, Taiwan, India, Pakistan and Vietnam.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-19th-international-medical-and-pharmaceutical-exhibition-vietnam-medi-pharm-expo', '', '', '2019-01-20 14:54:47', '2019-01-20 14:54:47', '', 0, 'http://medipharm.co/?p=577', 0, 'post', '', 0),
