(593, 1, '2019-01-20 15:11:21', '2019-01-20 15:11:21', '<em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Pursuant to the Law on Promulgation of Legal Documents of 2008;</span></span></em>\r\n\r\n<em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Pursuant to the 2005 Intellectual Property Law and the Law amending and supplementing a number of articles of the Intellectual Property Law of 2009;</span></span></em>\r\n\r\n<em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Pursuant to the Government''s Decree No. 103/2009 / ND-CP of November 6, 2009, promulgating the Regulation on public cultural activities and business services;</span></span></em>\r\n\r\n<em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Pursuant to the Government''s Decree No. 185/2007 / ND-CP of December 25, 2007, defining the functions, tasks, powers and organizational structure of the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism;</span></span></em>\r\n\r\n<em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          At the proposal of the Director of the Department of Fine Arts, Photography and Exhibition;</span></span></em>\r\n\r\n<em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          The Minister of Culture, Sports and Tourism issues a Circular regulating exhibitions, competitions, festivals and use of photographic works.</span></span></em>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">GENERAL PROVISIONS</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<strong><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Article 1. Scope</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">This Circular prescribes the following activities:</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">1. Exhibition of photographic works in Vietnam and bring photographic works from Vietnam to overseas exhibitions.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">2. Exam, festival of photographic works in Vietnam and take photographic works from Vietnam to abroad for competitions and festivals.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">3. Using photographic works in newspapers, publications, advertising products, to transfer materials or in combination with other art forms.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Article 2. Subjects of application</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">This Circular applies to Vietnamese organizations and individuals; </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Foreign organizations and individuals operating legally in Vietnam.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">In cases where an international treaty to which the Socialist Republic of Vietnam is a member contains different provisions, the provisions of such international treaty shall apply.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Article 3. Interpretation of terms</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">In this Circular, the terms below are construed as follows:</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">1.  </span></span><em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">A photographic</span></span></em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">  work is a work that shows the image of an objective world on light-emitting materials or on the means by which images are created or can be created by chemical, electronic or methodological methods. Other technical solutions.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">2.  </span></span><em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Material transfer</span></span></em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">  is a form of use of photographic works to represent materials other than the original material.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">3.  </span></span><em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Combined with other art forms</span></span></em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">  is the form of using a part or the whole of photographic works to create products of art type: art, theater, cinema and other forms.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">4.  </span></span><em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Publication and dissemination of photographic works</span></span></em><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">  means the bringing of photographic works to the public through exhibitions, screenings, uploading to the Internet, publishing in newspapers, publications and technical means. other visual effects.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Article 4. Acts prohibited in exhibitions, competitions, festivals and use of photographic works</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">1. Against the State of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam; </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">undermining the unity of the whole nation.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">2. Propagating violence, aggressive wars, hatred between peoples and peoples; </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">propagating reactionary ideology, lewd, depraved lifestyle, criminal acts, social evils, superstition, contrary to fine customs and habits, harming the health and destroying the ecological environment .</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">3. Disclosing secrets of the Party and State, military, security, economic and foreign relations secrets; </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">secret of personal privacy and other secrets prescribed by law.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">4. To pierce history, deny revolutionary achievements, offend great people, offend the nation, slander, offend honor, prestige of the organization, honor and dignity of individuals.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">5. Violating regulations on civilized lifestyle, security, order, fire prevention and fighting and other provisions of law.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">6. Violation of copyright and copyright-related rights for photographic works used.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">7. Use of photographic works with decisions on suspension of circulation, prohibition of circulation, withdrawal, confiscation and destruction of competent state agencies.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">          Article 5. Regulations for a number of related activities when organizing exhibitions, competitions and photographic festival festivals</span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Activities involved in organizing exhibitions, competitions, photography productions such as advertising, press conferences, performing arts, gymnastics, sports, entertainment, entertainment and other activities must comply with the law on such activities.</span></span>', 'The Circular provides for exhibitions, competitions, festivals and use of photographic works', 'Photographic work is a work that shows the image of the objective world on light-emitting materials or on the means by which images are created or can be created by chemical, electronic or thorough methods. another technique.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-circular-provides-for-exhibitions-competitions-festivals-and-use-of-photographic-works', '', '', '2019-01-20 15:11:21', '2019-01-20 15:11:21', '', 0, 'http://medipharm.co/?p=593', 0, 'post', '', 0),
