(596, 1, '2019-01-20 15:19:15', '2019-01-20 15:19:15', '<div><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Pursuant to the Law on T- </span></span></i><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">drive  </span></span></i><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">of the Government on June 19, 2015;</span></span></i></div>\r\n<div><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Pursuant to the November 26, 2014 Investment Law;</span></span></i></div>\r\n<div><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">At the request of Health Minister t </span></span></i><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">dull </span></span></i><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">;</span></span></i></div>\r\n<div><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">The Government issued a Decree on management of medical equipment </span></span></i><i><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">.</span></span></i></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span id="demuc1064251" class="demuc4"><a name="dieu_1"></a><b><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Article 1. Scope</span></span></b></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">This Decree regulates the management of medical equipment including: Classification of medical equipment; </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">production, circulation, sale and purchase of medical equipment services; </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">information and labels of medical equipment and management and use of medical equipment at medical establishments.</span></span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span id="demuc1064252" class="demuc4"><a name="dieu_2"></a><b><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Article 2. Interpretation of terms</span></span></b></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">1. Medical equipment are types of equipment, instruments, materials, implants, reagents and calibrators in vitro, software (software) used individually or in coordination with each other only of medical equipment owners to serve people for one or more of the following purposes:</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">a) Diagnose, prevent, monitor and treat and reduce disease or compensate for injuries and injuries;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">b) Check, replace, adjust or support anatomy and physiological processes;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">c) Support or maintain life;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">d) Control conception;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">d) Sterilizing medical equipment, including chemicals used in the testing process;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">e) Specialized transportation or use for medical activities;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">g) Provide information for the diagnosis, monitoring and treatment through measures to check samples derived from the human body.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">2. Medical equipment in vitro diagnostic medical device including reagents, calibrators, control materials, instruments, machines, equipment or systems used separately or in combination Indication of the owner to cater to the examination of specimens derived from the human body.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">3. An accessory is a product designated by a medical equipment owner for a specific purpose with a specific medical device to facilitate or support the device for the right purpose. Its intended.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">4. Medical equipment owners are organizations and individuals that perform the following tasks:</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">a) Providing medical equipment by their own name or by any other trademark, design, trade name or other name or other code owned or controlled by that individual or organization;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">b) Responsible for designing, manufacturing, assembling, processing, labeling, packaging or repairing medical equipment or determining the intended use of such medical equipment.</span></span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span id="demuc1064253" class="demuc4"><a name="dieu_3"></a><b><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Article 3. Principles for management of medical equipment</span></span></b></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">1. Ensuring the quality, safety and efficient use of medical equipment.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">2. Complete, accurate and timely information on technical characteristics, utility of medical equipment and risk factors that may occur to users.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">3. Ensuring traceability of medical equipment.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">4. Management of medical equipment must be based on the classification of risks and national standards, corresponding national technical regulations promulgated, recognized or caused by competent state management agencies. announced organizations and individuals shall comply with the provisions of law.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">5. Medical equipment being measuring devices and radiation equipment must be managed in accordance with the law on measurement, the law on atomic energy and the provisions of this Decree.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Chemicals and preparations with only one purpose are to disinfect managed medical equipment according to the provisions of this Decree. </span><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Chemicals and preparations with the purpose of disinfecting medical equipment but in addition to other uses are managed in accordance with the law on insecticidal and germicidal chemicals and preparations used in the field. Household and medical.</span></span></div>\r\n</div>', 'Nghị định về quản lý trang thiết bị y tế', 'Medical equipment being measuring devices and radiation equipment must be managed in accordance with the law on measurement, the law on atomic energy and the provisions of this Decree.\r\nChemicals and preparations with only one purpose are to disinfect managed medical equipment according to the provisions of this Decree. Chemicals and preparations with the purpose of disinfecting medical equipment but in addition to other uses are managed in accordance with the law on insecticidal and germicidal chemicals and preparations used in the field. Household and medical.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '479-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-20 15:19:15', '2019-01-20 15:19:15', '', 479, 'http://medipharm.co/479-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
