pment or determining the intended use of the medical device.</span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span id="demuc1064253" class="demuc4"><a name="dieu_3"></a><b><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Article 3. Principles of management of medical equipment</span></b></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">1. Ensuring quality, safety and effective use of medical equipment.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">2. Complete, accurate and timely information on technical characteristics, utility of medical equipment and risk factors that may occur to users.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">3. Ensure traceability of medical equipment.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">4. Management of medical equipment must be based on the classification of risks and national standards, relevant national technical regulations promulgated, recognized or caused by competent state management agencies. . Published organizations and individuals must comply with the provisions of the law.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">5. Medical equipment being measurement equipment and radiation equipment must be managed according to the provisions of law on atomic energy law and regulations and the provisions of this Decree.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Chemicals and preparations with a single purpose are to disinfect managed medical equipment in accordance with this Decree. Chemicals and preparations for disinfection of medical equipment but other than those used for other purposes are governed by the legislation on insecticidal and germicidal chemicals and preparations used in the field. this area. Household and medical.</span></div>\r\n</div>', 'Decree on management of medical equipment', 'Medical equipment being measuring devices and radiation equipment must be managed in accordance with the law on measurement, the law on atomic energy and the provisions of this Decree.\r\nChemicals and preparations with only one purpose are to disinfect managed medical equipment according to the provisions of this Decree. Chemicals and preparations with the purpose of disinfecting medical equipment but in addition to other uses are managed in accordance with the law on insecticidal and germicidal chemicals and preparations used in the field. Household and medical.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '599-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-01-20 15:20:35', '2019-01-20 15:20:35', '', 599, 'http://medipharm.co/599-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(601, 1, '2019-01-20 15:26:22', '2019-01-20 15:26:22', '<p class="abs"><span style="vertical-align: inherit;">On December 20, the Drug Administration of Vietnam (Ministry of Health) updated the list of domestic drug production facilities meeting good production practice standards (GMP-WHO) granted Certificate by the Drug Administration of Vietnam.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="wrapper-main-content"><article class="_photo-content summary">\r\n<div class="article-content">\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Accordingly, as of December 18, 222 domestic drug manufacturing establishments up to GMP-WHO standards have been granted certificates by the Drug Administration of Vietnam.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">From the beginning of 2018 until now, the Drug Administration of Vietnam has issued GMP-WHO certificates to 11 drug manufacturing establishments.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">That is Sun Garden Vietnam Company Limited; Thanh Phat Pharmaceutical Joint Stock Company; PQA Pharmaceutical Joint Stock Company; Ha Nam Pharmaceutical and Medical Supplies Joint Stock Company; Traphacosapa One Member Company Limited; Ha Thanh Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd; Saigon Pharmaceutical Company Limited (Sapharco); Novaglory Company Limited; Southeastern Truong Son pharmaceutical joint stock company; Nippon Chemiphar Vietnam Company Limited; Mekophar Company Limited.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">In order to harmonize international standards of GMP and promote export and cooperation with countries around the world in this field, the Ministry of Health has decided, from July 1, 2008, new drug manufacturing facilities Pharmacists permitted to produce must meet GMP-WHO principles and standards.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">At the same time, the Ministry also encourages drug manufacturers from medicinal materials to apply this principle and standard.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">GMP (Good Manufacturing Practices) is a guide to good manufacturing practices, applicable to food production, processing and pharmaceutical establishments to control factors affecting the process of product quality formation from the stage. designing, installing workshops, equipment and processing tools; service conditions, preparation for processing to processing; packaging, storage and people control activities during processing and processing.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Many recent shocks in the country and abroad in the field of health products are very worrying. Counterfeit drugs still exist in the market. The above facts require pharmaceutical manufacturers to pay attention to managing the quality system during the production process of the factory. Quality control of production process and pharmaceutical quality is a continuous, long-term, non-stop process with increasing requirements.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">Good production practices include general principles, regulations and guidelines on basic contents of production conditions; Applicable to establishments producing, processing, packaging food, pharmaceuticals, medical equipment, cosmetics ..., to ensure products of quality and safety.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">GMP is concerned with important factors: people, materials, machinery, operations, environment in all areas of the manufacturing process, including the issue of customer complaints. and recall the wrong product.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="vertical-align: inherit;">GMP requirements are broad and general, allowing each manufacturer to make their own decisions about the number of regulations, standards, procedures, and work instructions to meet the necessary requirements. suitable to the type, field of production and facilities of the enterprise. Therefore, the number of regulations and procedures of the GMP system of each enterprise will be different.</span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</article></div>', '222 drug production facilities meet good production practice standards', 'Good production practices include general principles, regulations and guidelines on basic contents of production conditions; Applicable to establishments producing, processing, packaging food, pharmaceuticals, medical equipment, cosmetics ..., to ensure products of quality and safety.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '222-drug-production-facilities-meet-good-production-practice-standards', '', '', '2019-01-20 15:26:22', '2019-01-20 15:26:22', '', 0, 'http://medipharm.co/?p=601', 0, 'post', '', 0),
